data.name: ServicesControlCodesHelpText
data.value:
The commands accepted by services are:
SERVICE_ACCEPT_NETBINDCHANGE: the service accepts changes in its network bindings without having to restart SERVICE_ACCEPT_PARAMCHANGE: the service can reread its startup parameters without having to restart SERVICE_ACCEPT_PAUSE_CONTINUE: the service can be paused and continued SERVICE_ACCEPT_PRESHUTDOWN: the service can run pre-shutdown tasks SERVICE_ACCEPT_SHUTDOWN: the service is notified when the system is shutting down SERVICE_ACCEPT_STOP: the service can be stopped SERVICE_ACCEPT_HARDWAREPROFILECHANGE: the service is notified when the computer's hardware profile has changed SERVICE_ACCEPT_POWEREVENT: the service is notified when the computer's power status has changed SERVICE_ACCEPT_SESSIONCHANGE: the service is notified when the computer's sessione status has changed SERVICE_ACCEPT_TIMECHANGE: the system time has changed SERVICE_ACCEPT_TRIGGER_EVENT SERVICE_ACCEPT_USER_LOGOFF: user disconnected SERVICE_ACCEPT_LOWRESOURCES: low resources SERVICE_ACCEPT_SYSTEM_LOW_RESOURCES: low system resources
